spans.text: the spoil of every distant age
each human virtue thine , By MANLIUS , by me , by all esteemed divine
of the silent dead , And at a much loved sister's hallowed bier
mark yonder aged venerable band Who round their HARRIET's grave , in sorrow
death alas ! their woes revive , Again with penury they're doomed to strive
who now shall cheer their drooping age
their sorrows cease , And smooth their passage to the realms of peace
smooth their passage to the realms of peace
what form majestic now appears , Oppressed by sorrow and dissolved in tears
the wretched train , Who now in solemn silence homeward turn , And quit , reluctant quit
Who now in solemn silence homeward turn , And quit
the spot , not changed the scene
But mark ! though changed the spot , not changed the scene , Nor yet their bosoms
soon bid cease , Soon may their tortured souls be hushed to peace
their tortured souls be hushed to peace
their tortured souls be hushed to peace
viewest with pleasure the surrounding gloom
beneath its sadly drooping shade There rest the ashes of a lovely maid , If virtuous worth be heaven's peculiar care , She does its brightest , noblest pleasures share
the ashes of a lovely maid
The unfrequented paths of virtue tread
